{
  "$schema": "../../shared/schemas/dev-workflow-rules.schema.json",
  "schema_version": 1,
  "summary": "Repo development workflow routing rules for changed files.",
  "rules": [
    {
      "id": "app-subtree-local-contract",
      "summary": "App subtree changes delegate app-specific workflow details to the nearest local contract.",
      "patterns": [
        "apps/**"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "app",
        "local_contract"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "read_local_contract"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [],
      "verification": [],
      "notes": [
        "Repo-wide routing should not encode app-specific behavior; read the nearest subtree AGENTS.md or local playbook before choosing app tests."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "swift-core",
      "summary": "Unified aos binary or Swift IPC sources changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "src/**/*.swift",
        "shared/swift/ipc/**/*.swift"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "swift",
        "aos_binary"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "swift_build"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": false,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": true,
      "commands": [],
      "verification": [],
      "notes": [
        "If the repo-local ./aos binary is missing or exits 137, recover with `bash build.sh --force --no-restart` because the normal post-build verification cannot run through a broken ./aos artifact.",
        "ADR 0023 requires root build.sh with inline source fingerprinting and one plain direct swiftc link. Injected plist or metadata sections, separate linking, post-link signing, explicit identifiers, entitlements, copying, moving, binary rewriting, app wrapping, and spctl gates are prohibited.",
        "The router intentionally does not schedule the TCC-sensitive build or first launch beside ordinary checks. Finish all static commands first; then use the `aos-repo-binary-build` skill for the isolated build checkpoint.",
        "At that checkpoint, run `bash build.sh --force --no-restart`, then run `./aos help --json` as the immediately following command and stop on exit 137.",
        "After help succeeds, stop until the user manually regrants TCC and replies `finished`; then run exact `./aos ready --repair --post-permission --json` with no intervening command."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "repo-build-tooling",
      "summary": "Repo-mode build wrapper, signing, or rebuild alert behavior changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "build.sh",
        "scripts/aos-after-build",
        "scripts/aos-dev-build.mjs",
        "tests/aos-after-build.sh",
        "tests/aos-build-attestation.test.mjs",
        "tests/build-rebuild-policy.sh"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "build_tooling",
        "aos_binary"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "focused_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "build-rebuild-policy-test",
          "command": "bash tests/build-rebuild-policy.sh",
          "reason": "Verify content-based one-link rebuilds, no post-link mutation, and the help-first launch checkpoint."
        }
      ],
      "verification": [],
      "notes": [
        "The raw recovery command for a missing or launch-killed repo ./aos is `bash build.sh --force --no-restart`; do not repair it with a separate linker or post-link mutation.",
        "After a real rebuild, ./aos help --json is the exact first launch. If it succeeds, stop for the human TCC checkpoint before any inspection or readiness command. spctl rejection is expected for the repo-local raw shape and is not an acceptance gate."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "root-skill-packages",
      "summary": "Root skill package instructions or registry-backed skill contracts changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "skills/**",
        "scripts/aos-skills*.mjs",
        "tests/aos-skills-*.test.mjs"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "skills"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "skill_validation"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "skills-validate",
          "command": "node scripts/aos-skills-validate.mjs --json",
          "reason": "Validate root skill package metadata, body budgets, durable backing, and install target support."
        },
        {
          "id": "skills-registry-test",
          "command": "node --test tests/aos-skills-registry.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify root skill registry coverage and split-skill contracts."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "toolkit-components",
      "summary": "Reusable toolkit component or runtime browser code changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "packages/toolkit/components/**",
        "packages/toolkit/contracts/mounted-surface-menu-projection.js",
        "packages/toolkit/panel/**",
        "packages/toolkit/runtime/**",
        "packages/toolkit/status-item/**",
        "packages/toolkit/package.json",
        "packages/toolkit/package-lock.json"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "toolkit",
        "web_surface"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "component_reload",
        "focused_toolkit_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "status-item-contract",
      "summary": "Native status-item host, public toolkit, schema, or CLI transport changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "manifests/commands/source/aos/40-status-item.json",
        "manifests/commands/source/external/48-status-item.json",
        "packages/toolkit/status-item/**",
        "scripts/aos-status-item.mjs",
        "scripts/lib/status-item-output-writer.mjs",
        "shared/schemas/aos-status-item-*.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/daemon-request.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/daemon-response.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/daemon-event.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/fixtures/daemon-event/**/status-item-*.json",
        "src/display/status-item*.swift"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "status_item",
        "command_contract"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "focused_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "status-item-contract",
          "command": "node --test tests/status-item-contract.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Status-item production sources must retain schema, native host, transport, and bounded follow-stream coverage."
        },
        {
          "id": "status-item-daemon-schemas",
          "command": "bash tests/daemon-ipc-schema.sh && node --test tests/schemas/daemon-event.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Canonical request, response, and event envelopes must retain strict status-item wire validation."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "desktop-annotation-selection",
      "summary": "Native desktop annotation selection, persistence projection, or semantic target contract changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "manifests/commands/source/aos/03-see-04-annotation.json",
        "scripts/aos-annotation-select.mjs",
        "scripts/lib/pending-annotations-model.mjs",
        "shared/schemas/aos-pending-annotation-v0.*",
        "shared/schemas/daemon-event.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/fixtures/daemon-event/**/annotation-*.json",
        "src/daemon/annotation-selection.swift",
        "src/daemon/annotation-target-selection.swift",
        "src/perceive/ax.swift",
        "tests/annotation-select-cli.test.mjs",
        "tests/annotation-selection-native.sh",
        "tests/schemas/aos-pending-annotation-v0.test.mjs",
        "tests/schemas/daemon-event.test.mjs",
        "tests/toolkit/pending-annotation-model.test.mjs"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "desktop_annotation",
        "command_contract",
        "schema",
        "swift"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "focused_test",
        "schema_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": false,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": true,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "annotation-selection-adapter",
          "command": "node --test tests/annotation-select-cli.test.mjs && bash tests/annotation-selection-native.sh",
          "reason": "Verify strict follow-stream persistence, redaction, singleton ownership, bounded geometry, semantic drill-down, and admission-only TCC checks."
        },
        {
          "id": "annotation-selection-schema",
          "command": "node --test tests/schemas/aos-pending-annotation-v0.test.mjs tests/schemas/daemon-event.test.mjs tests/toolkit/pending-annotation-model.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify target mode and element evidence remain closed, bounded, mode-matched, and path-free."
        },
        {
          "id": "annotation-selection-command-manifest",
          "command": "bash tests/command-manifest-generation.sh",
          "reason": "Keep geometric and semantic target form identifiers explicit in generated help."
        }
      ],
      "verification": [],
      "notes": [
        "Run these static and fake-daemon checks before the isolated repo-binary rebuild checkpoint; never use the live daemon or TCC as part of this route."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "desktop-world-scene-engine",
      "summary": "DesktopWorld scene contracts, authoring tools, runtime session, extensions, or agent route changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "packages/toolkit/scene/**",
        "packages/toolkit/components/desktop-world-stage/**",
        "src/daemon/desktop-world-scene-*.swift",
        "src/daemon/scene-event.swift",
        "src/daemon/scene-lease-registry.swift",
        "src/daemon/unified.swift",
        "src/display/desktop-world-surface.swift",
        "scripts/aos-scene.mjs",
        "scripts/lib/aos-scene-*.mjs",
        "manifests/commands/source/aos/39-scene.json",
        "manifests/commands/source/external/47-scene.json",
        "docs/api/toolkit/scene*.md",
        "tests/scene-*.test.mjs",
        "tests/desktop-world-scene-event-routing.test.mjs",
        "tests/desktop-world-scene-result-coordinator.test.mjs",
        "tests/daemon-desktop-world-devtools-contract.test.mjs",
        "tests/toolkit/desktop-world-scene-*.test.mjs",
        "tests/toolkit/desktop-world-session.test.mjs",
        "tests/toolkit/scene-*.test.mjs"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "toolkit",
        "command_contract",
        "scene_engine"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "focused_test",
        "help_contract"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "scene-daemon-contract",
          "command": "node --test tests/desktop-world-scene-event-routing.test.mjs tests/desktop-world-scene-result-coordinator.test.mjs tests/daemon-desktop-world-devtools-contract.test.mjs tests/scene-follow-cli.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify canonical event routing diagnostics, the daemon scene lifecycle aggregate, all-segment barrier ownership, DevTools delegation, and bounded follow transport."
        },
        {
          "id": "scene-core-contract",
          "command": "node --test tests/toolkit/desktop-world-client.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-cartridge.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-document.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-generic-three.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-host.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-public-contract.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify the canonical document, cartridge, transaction, host, generic projection, client, and focused package boundaries."
        },
        {
          "id": "scene-interaction-contract",
          "command": "node --test tests/toolkit/scene-interaction.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-radial-menu.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-interaction-visual.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-historical-fast-travel-reference.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-scene-interaction-runtime.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-scene-interaction-three.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-scene-operation-coordinator.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-scene-outlet.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify gesture arbitration, native-region atomicity, generic responses, fixed-clock visuals, historical references, and bounded Three lifecycle."
        },
        {
          "id": "scene-devtools-contract",
          "command": "node --test tests/toolkit/desktop-world-devtools-model.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-devtools-view.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-devtools-compat.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify host-neutral DevTools state, views, compatibility projections, bounded telemetry, and disabled instrumentation cost."
        },
        {
          "id": "scene-agent-authoring-contract",
          "command": "node --test tests/toolkit/desktop-world-session.test.mjs tests/toolkit/scene-public-contract.test.mjs tests/toolkit/toolkit-api-docs-contract.test.mjs tests/scene-scaffold-cli.test.mjs tests/scene-agent-authoring-acceptance.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify the high-level session, focused exports, deterministic scaffolds, split guides, and empty-directory agent route."
        },
        {
          "id": "scene-extension-contract",
          "command": "node --test tests/toolkit/scene-extension.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-scene-extension-loader.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-scene-extension-operation.test.mjs tests/toolkit/desktop-world-scene-extension-projection.test.mjs tests/scene-extension-cli.test.mjs tests/scene-extension-native-store.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify reviewed extension identity, validation, loading, operation, projection, immutable storage, and disposal."
        },
        {
          "id": "scene-command-help-contract",
          "command": "bash tests/help-contract.sh",
          "reason": "Keep scene source manifests, generated help, examples, and dispatch metadata aligned."
        }
      ],
      "verification": [],
      "notes": [
        "These checks are static or fake-transport only; do not build or execute the repo AOS binary for this route."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "experience-runtime-contract",
      "summary": "Experience manifest normalization or runtime-context contracts changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "scripts/aos-experience.mjs",
        "scripts/lib/experience-manifest.mjs",
        "scripts/lib/experience-runtime*.mjs",
        "shared/schemas/aos-experience-v*.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/aos-experience-runtime-context-v*.*"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "experience_runtime",
        "command_contract"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "focused_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "experience-runtime-contract",
          "command": "node --test --test-concurrency=1 tests/experience-runtime-context-content-roots.test.mjs tests/experience-runtime-context-env.test.mjs tests/experience-runtime-context-pending-annotations.test.mjs tests/experience-runtime-context-probes.test.mjs tests/schemas/aos-experience-runtime-context-v0.test.mjs tests/schemas/aos-experience-runtime-context-v1.test.mjs tests/schemas/aos-experience-v1.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Experience production sources must retain frozen v0 compatibility and the active status-item-free v1 contract."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "browser-intent-sensor",
      "summary": "Browser intent sensor or JS adapter path changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "packages/toolkit/browser-intent-sensor/**"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "toolkit",
        "browser_intent_sensor"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "focused_js_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "browser-intent-test",
          "command": "node --test packages/toolkit/browser-intent-sensor",
          "reason": "Browser intent sensor changes stay in the JavaScript test loop unless an adapter contract changes."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "schemas",
      "summary": "Shared schema contracts changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "shared/schemas/**",
        "scripts/generate-input-event-validator.mjs"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "schema"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "schema_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "schema-tests",
          "command": "node --test tests/schemas/*.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Schema changes should run schema validation tests without daemon restart."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "command-surface-manifests",
      "summary": "Command metadata or external command manifest changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "manifests/commands/*.json",
        "manifests/commands/source/**",
        "scripts/generate-command-manifests.mjs",
        "shared/schemas/aos-external-command-manifest-v0.schema.json",
        "tests/schemas/aos-external-command-manifest-v0.test.mjs",
        "tests/command-manifest-generation.sh",
        "tests/aos-dev-gh-help-parity.test.mjs",
        "tests/external-command-dispatch.sh",
        "tests/help-contract.sh"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "command_contract",
        "schema"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "schema_test",
        "help_contract",
        "focused_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "command-manifest-generation",
          "command": "bash tests/command-manifest-generation.sh",
          "reason": "Source command manifests and generated command artifacts must stay in sync."
        },
        {
          "id": "external-command-manifest-schema",
          "command": "node --test tests/schemas/aos-external-command-manifest-v0.test.mjs",
          "reason": "External command manifest changes must preserve launcher schema, script targets, and help-manifest route coverage."
        },
        {
          "id": "external-command-dispatch",
          "command": "bash tests/external-command-dispatch.sh",
          "reason": "Manifest-backed command routes must still dispatch through external modules."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-gh-help-parity",
          "command": "node --test tests/aos-dev-gh-help-parity.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Repo-local GitHub helper subcommands must stay dispatchable through direct script help."
        },
        {
          "id": "help-contract",
          "command": "bash tests/help-contract.sh",
          "reason": "Command metadata and manifests must stay aligned with discoverable help and parser contracts."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "command-surface-implementations",
      "summary": "Hot-swappable external command implementation changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "scripts/aos-*.mjs",
        "scripts/aos-*",
        "scripts/lib/status-item-output-writer.mjs",
        "scripts/lib/aos-ready-*.mjs",
        "scripts/lib/aos-readiness.mjs",
        "scripts/sign-aos-runtime",
        "packages/cli/**",
        "packages/gateway/dist/doctor-cli.js"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "command_contract",
        "command_implementation"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "focused_test",
        "help_contract"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "external-command-dispatch",
          "command": "bash tests/external-command-dispatch.sh",
          "reason": "External command implementation changes must keep manifest dispatch and wrapper integration intact."
        },
        {
          "id": "external-parser-flags",
          "command": "bash tests/external-parser-flags.sh",
          "reason": "External command wrappers should reject malformed flags and arguments before falling through to Swift primitives."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-gh-help-parity",
          "command": "node --test tests/aos-dev-gh-help-parity.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Repo-local GitHub helper subcommands must stay dispatchable through direct script help."
        },
        {
          "id": "help-contract",
          "command": "bash tests/help-contract.sh",
          "reason": "Command implementation changes must stay aligned with discoverable help and parser contracts."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "dev-gh-helper",
      "summary": "Repo-local GitHub helper implementation or contract changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "scripts/aos-dev-gh.mjs",
        "scripts/aos-dev-gh-spec.mjs",
        "tests/aos-dev-gh-contract.test.mjs",
        "tests/aos-dev-gh-help-parity.test.mjs"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "command_contract",
        "dev_workflow"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "focused_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "dev-gh-contract",
          "command": "node --test tests/aos-dev-gh-contract.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify the repo-local GitHub helper wraps only the sanctioned non-interactive gh subset."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-gh-help-parity",
          "command": "node --test tests/aos-dev-gh-help-parity.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Verify the repo-local GitHub helper allowlist and direct script help stay aligned."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "dev-workflow-manifest",
      "summary": "Developer workflow router manifest or tests changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "docs/dev/workflow-rules.json",
        "docs/dev/agent-capabilities.json",
        "docs/dev/active-profile.json",
        "docs/dev/test-proof-registry.json",
        "docs/dev/test-proof-registry.d/**",
        "docs/dev/workflow-profiles.json",
        "docs/dev/workflow-profiles/**",
        "scripts/aos-dev-workflow.mjs",
        "scripts/aos-dev-situation.mjs",
        "scripts/aos-dev-drift-lint.mjs",
        "scripts/lib/dev-test-proof-registry.mjs",
        "shared/schemas/dev-test-proof-registry.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/fixtures/dev-test-proof-registry/**",
        "shared/schemas/dev-workflow-rules.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/fixtures/dev-workflow-rules/**",
        "shared/schemas/dev-active-profile.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/dev-workflow-profiles.md",
        "shared/schemas/dev-workflow-profiles.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/fixtures/dev-workflow-profiles/**",
        "tests/dev-workflow-router.sh",
        "tests/dev-audit.sh",
        "tests/dev-situation.sh",
        "tests/dev-drift-lint.sh",
        "tests/schemas/dev-test-proof-registry.test.mjs",
        "tests/schemas/dev-workflow-rules.test.mjs",
        "tests/schemas/dev-active-profile.test.mjs",
        "tests/schemas/dev-workflow-profiles.test.mjs"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "dev_workflow",
        "schema"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "schema_test"
      ],
      "hot_swappable": true,
      "tcc_identity_sensitive": false,
      "commands": [
        {
          "id": "dev-test-proof-registry-schema-test",
          "command": "node --test tests/schemas/dev-test-proof-registry.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Validate the proof-worth registry, fixtures, and focused evaluator behavior."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-workflow-schema-test",
          "command": "node --test tests/schemas/dev-workflow-rules.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Validate the router manifest and fixtures against the schema."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-active-profile-schema-test",
          "command": "node --test tests/schemas/dev-active-profile.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Validate the active development integration profile selector and its referenced profile."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-workflow-profile-schema-test",
          "command": "node --test tests/schemas/dev-workflow-profiles.test.mjs",
          "reason": "Validate the workflow profiles manifest and fixtures against the schema."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-workflow-router-test",
          "command": "bash tests/dev-workflow-router.sh",
          "reason": "Verify the maintainer workflow parser, proof-worth ratchet, and manifest-backed recommendations agree."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-audit-test",
          "command": "bash tests/dev-audit.sh",
          "reason": "Verify the maintainer workflow audit reports evidence-backed pass and fail claims."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-situation-test",
          "command": "bash tests/dev-situation.sh",
          "reason": "Verify live orientation packets preserve per-source status, source traces, and no-synthesis partial failures."
        },
        {
          "id": "dev-drift-lint-test",
          "command": "bash tests/dev-drift-lint.sh",
          "reason": "Verify the heuristic durable-status tripwire distinguishes historical blocks from unmarked standing claims."
        }
      ],
      "verification": []
    },
    {
      "id": "agent-capability-manifest",
      "summary": "Agent capability manifest schema, canonical manifest, or tests changed.",
      "patterns": [
        "docs/dev/agent-capabilities.json",
        "shared/schemas/aos-agent-capability-manifest-v0.md",
        "shared/schemas/aos-agent-capability-manifest-v0.schema.json",
        "shared/schemas/fixtures/aos-agent-capability-manifest-v0/**",
        "tests/schemas/aos-agent-capability-manifest-v0.test.mjs"
      ],
      "classes": [
        "capability_manifest",
        "schema"
      ],
      "actions": [
        "schema_test",
        "focused_test"
      ],
